Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim @green beans{6%oz} if necessary. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating
whites from greens. Strip @thyme{1%tsp} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves.
Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and
@black pepper{}. Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion
whites; cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of salt. Bring to a
boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, pat @chicken cutlets{12%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season all
over with @paprika{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken
and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If chicken begins to brown too quickly, lower the heat.

Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in same pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add chopped
thyme; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup}. Bring to a simmer,
then immediately turn off heat.

Stir in @sour cream{1.5%tbsp} and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lemon zest and @pistachios{1/2%oz}. Season with
salt and pepper.

Divide rice, green beans, and chicken between plates. Top chicken with sauce and
sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.